{
  "doc_id": "3903",
  "text": "Because D2 expression has been demonstrated to be regulated by TSH in human thyroid gland and rat brown adipose tissue [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , we studied the effects of TSH on D2 mRNA and D2 activity in SaOS-2 and NHOst cells. D2 mRNA and D2 activities in SaOS-2 cells (Fig. 5, A and B) and NHOst cells (Fig. 5 , C and D) were significantly increased by TSH in a dose-dependent manner. These results indicate that D2 expression is pretranslationally regulated by a TSH receptor-cAMP-mediated mechanism in SaOS-2 and NHOst cells.",
